  "text": "In the present study, occult lymph node metastasis did not correlate with elevated risk of locoregional recurrence or remote metastasis. Regional evolution was observed in only 4 cases (2 pN-and 2 pN+; 2.4%), compared to 5.5% of cases reported by Lim et al. [CITATION_1] . Regional recurrence often involves levels II and III [CITATION_2] . In the present study, survival was significantly poorer in pN+ than pN-patients on multivariate analysis, pN stage having greater prognostic impact than tumor stage.",
